This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new framework for matrix factorization using a variational auto-encoder. It also falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with collaborative filtering in recommendation systems. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the use of neural networks to capture complex mappings. Computer vision (cs.CV) could also be a relevant sub-category as matrix factorization is often used in image and video processing. Finally, it could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) as recommendation systems are often used in social networks.
